and the life of my brother.

512
00:53:48.324 --> 00:53:50.315
OK.

513
00:53:51.964 --> 00:53:53.556
OK.

514
00:53:54.564 --> 00:53:58.352
I give you your brother. you give me the girl.

515
00:53:58.444 --> 00:54:01.163
- All right.
- Where?

516
00:54:15.245 --> 00:54:19.443
He left the roof. We lost the signal.

517
00:54:19.525 --> 00:54:21.004
We got cut off.

518
00:54:22.845 --> 00:54:24.597
We lost him. We lost him.

519
00:54:26.806 --> 00:54:27.716
Damn.

520
00:54:44.166 --> 00:54:47.476
- Hello?
- Lisa. listen to me. Don't hang up.

521
00:54:47.566 --> 00:54:49.558
I think Pita's alive.

522
00:54:51.407 --> 00:54:53.602
I can't take this any more.

523
00:54:53.687 --> 00:54:58.363
Take the road to Puebla.
Get off junction 34. south side.

524
00:54:58.447 --> 00:55:00.438
I'll meet you there in two hours.

525
00:55:44.489 --> 00:55:46.719
So where is she?

526
00:55:48.129 --> 00:55:52.327
She's right over there.
You see those two cars out there?

527
00:55:57.410 --> 00:55:59.401
Pita's kidnapper. Daniel...

528
00:56:00.570 --> 00:56:02.686
Here's his brother.

529
00:56:04.490 --> 00:56:06.048
Here.

530
00:56:07.050 --> 00:56:09.689
I'm goin' up on the bridge to get Pita.

531
00:56:09.770 --> 00:56:13.888
Anything goes wrong. you put it to his head.

532
00:56:13.970 --> 00:56:16.929
you pull the trigger. all right?

533
00:56:17.011 --> 00:56:19.445
You understand?

534
00:56:22.211 --> 00:56:26.648
You don't let him loose

535
00:56:26.731 --> 00:56:29.404
until she's with you. you got it?

536
00:56:32.211 --> 00:56:34.850
And you don't wait for me. OK?

537
00:56:38.091 --> 00:56:41.129
- Yeah.
- You'll be all right. You OK?

538
00:56:41.212 --> 00:56:42.645
Yeah.

539
00:58:23.656 --> 00:58:25.328
Creasy!

540
00:58:26.856 --> 00:58:28.848
Creasy!

541
00:58:29.977 --> 00:58:32.411
Creasy!

542
00:58:48.817 --> 00:58:50.297
- You all right?
- Yeah.

543
00:58:50.378 --> 00:58:53.017
They didn't hurt you?

544
00:58:54.458 --> 00:58:56.449
Hi.

545
00:58:57.938 --> 00:59:02.090
All right. your mother's waiting for you.
She's at the end the bridge.

546
00:59:02.178 --> 00:59:05.648
- OK. you go home.
- OK.

547
00:59:05.738 --> 00:59:08.536
- All right.
- Where are you going?

548
00:59:11.858 --> 00:59:13.850
I'm goin' home too.

549
00:59:15.779 --> 00:59:17.292
I'm goin' to Blue Bayou.

550
00:59:24.219 --> 00:59:26.210
I got something for you.

551
00:59:29.059 --> 00:59:31.129
I got the last number too.

552
00:59:32.459 --> 00:59:33.938
I love you. Creasy.

553
00:59:37.340 --> 00:59:39.570
And you love me. don't you?

554
00:59:39.660 --> 00:59:41.935
Yes. I do.

555
00:59:42.020 --> 00:59:44.090
Now. come on. Pita. go.

556
00:59:45.100 --> 00:59:47.091
- Go. Run.
- Bye.

